Create tar archive
$ tar cf <name of output> <file to create archive from>

Example
$ tar cf my_directory.tar my_directory

Here, 'my_directory' is the input file, 'my_directory.tar' is the
archive that is output by the operation.

List contents of archive
$ tar tf <name of tar archive>

Extract archive
$ tar xf <name of tar archive>
The contents are copied to the current directory.
Note: the extracted files take on the ownership of the user
performing the restoration.
